              },
              "sortBy": [],
              "noDataMessage": "No clusters returned by Azure Resource Graph. Verify your subscription filter and that your Azure Local clusters have completed Arc onboarding.",
              "noDataMessageStyle": 4
            },
            "name": "capacity-overview-table"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "💡 **Tip:** The 'Cluster Capacity Overview' table above uses data from **Azure Resource Graph (ARG)** to show high-level capacity at a glance — no Azure Monitor / Log Analytics Workspace required. All other tables and charts on the 'Capacity' tab *(and its sub-tabs)* draw on **Azure Monitor performance counters**, which yield more accurate memory usage and additionally cover **Hyper-V (unmanaged) VMs** that ARG does not see — on top of the Azure Local VMs and AKS Arc clusters that ARG already reports.\r\n\r\n⚠️ **Storage columns caveat:** Azure Local provisions **Thin** volumes by default, so the 'Storage Available' and 'Storage Used %' columns reflect each volume's *thin maximum* (a logical ceiling), not real pool-level headroom — the sum of thin maximums can exceed physical pool capacity, which is why these numbers can disagree with the Portal and WAC. Use PowerShell if you require accurate pool-level ***real available*** capacity *(with capacity-reserve and resiliency-factor adjustments)*, an EXAMPLE script is available here: [S2D-Show-Used-Available-Storage](https://github.com/NeilBird/Azure-Local/tree/main/S2D-Show-Used-Available-Storage).\r\n\r\nℹ️ **N-1 Memory Risk %:** This column estimates memory headroom if **one node** were lost (e.g. during a platform update or hardware failure). Single-machine clusters cannot tolerate a node loss, so the column shows '**No HA resiliency**' — workloads will go offline whenever the single host is rebooted (e.g. for monthly Azure Local updates).",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "name": "capacity-arg-vs-monitor-tip"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "---\r\n## 🔔 Performance Counter DCR Configuration\r\n💡 **Tip:** The six charts below require a **Data Collection Rule (DCR)** that collects specific Windows performance counters from your Azure Local nodes via the Azure Monitor Agent (AMA). Some counters (notably `Cluster CSV File System(*)` for CSV storage) are **not in the Azure Portal's preset dropdown**, but you can add them in the portal using the **Custom counter specifier** input on an existing DCR — this is the safest option because it adds to, rather than replaces, your current counters. Expand the section for step-by-step guidance; an ARM / CLI alternative is available via a nested **🛠️ Show Alternative ARM / CLI Deployment** toggle inside.\r\n\r\n> *Wondering why these LENS charts are empty when **Cluster Insights** or the cluster's **Monitoring → Metrics** blade already show storage numbers? Those views use Microsoft-managed pipelines (Arc VM Insights' auto-DCR + Azure Monitor platform metrics) that bypass your Log Analytics workspace. LENS reads your workspace — so it can only show what your DCR is collecting. Expand the **Show DCR Setup Guide** below for the full explanation and counter list.*"
            },
            "name": "text-dcr-setup-header"
          },
          {
            "type": 9,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
              "parameters": [
                {
                  "id": "dcr-setup-toggle",
                  "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                  "name": "ShowDCRSetupSection",
                  "label": "Show DCR Setup Guide",
                  "type": 10,
                  "isRequired": true,
                  "typeSettings": {
                    "additionalResourceOptions": [],
                    "showDefault": false
                  },
                  "jsonData": "[{\"value\": \"yes\", \"label\": \"Yes - Show DCR Setup\"}, {\"value\": \"no\", \"label\": \"No - Hide DCR Setup\"}]",
                  "value": "no"
                }
              ],
              "style": "pills",
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces"
            },
            "name": "dcr-setup-toggle-param"
          },
          {
            "type": 12,
            "content": {
              "version": "NotebookGroup/1.0",
              "groupType": "editable",
              "items": [
                {
                  "type": 1,
                  "content": {
                    "json": "### ❓ Why does LENS need DCR work when Cluster Insights / the Monitoring blade *already* show storage numbers?\r\n\r\nIt's a great question, and a common point of confusion — Cluster Insights and the LENS workbook read from **completely different telemetry pipelines**:\r\n\r\n| View | Data source | Who configures it |\r\n|------|-------------|-------------------|\r\n| **Cluster Insights** (the *Insights* blade on the Azure Local resource) | `InsightsMetrics` table, populated by the **Arc VM Insights** extension via a **Microsoft-managed DCR** that auto-deploys with the extension. Cluster-level CSV health surfaces from the SDDC management providers running on the cluster itself, rendered by a pre-canned Microsoft workbook. | Microsoft (auto-managed) |\r\n| **Azure Local resource blade → Monitoring → Metrics** | **Azure Monitor *platform* metrics** — counters lifted off the host by the Azure Local resource provider. **Doesn't flow through Log Analytics at all**, so no customer DCR is involved. | Microsoft (built into the RP) |\r\n| **LENS workbook** *(this dashboard)* | The customer's own **Log Analytics workspace** — which contains only the rows your DCR told AMA to collect, plus optional `InsightsMetrics` when VM Insights is enabled. | **You** (customer-managed DCR) |\r\n\r\n**Why does the gap exist?** The Azure Portal DCR wizard offers a fixed dropdown of generic Windows-server performance objects — `Processor`, `LogicalDisk`, `Memory`, `Network Interface`, etc. It **does not list** `Cluster CSV File System` or `Cluster Shared Volume`, which are the Azure-Local-specific S2D counters that report real CSV capacity, latency, and IOPS. So most customers end up with a DCR that collects OS-drive (`LogicalDisk`) data only — Cluster Insights and the Monitoring blade fill the gap silently via Microsoft-managed pipelines, but LENS can only show what *your* workspace contains.\r\n\r\n**Bottom line:** add the five `Cluster CSV File System(*)` counter paths via **Custom counter specifier** (the recommended method below) and the LENS Storage % / Latency / IOPS / forecast charts will populate within minutes.\r\n\r\n---",
                    "style": "info"
                  },
                  "name": "dcr-setup-why-faq"
                },
                {
                  "type": 1,
                  "content": {
                    "json": "### 📋 Prerequisites for the Capacity DCR\r\n\r\n1. **Azure Monitor Agent (AMA)** installed on each Azure Local node (deployed as an Arc extension on the `Microsoft.HybridCompute/machines` resource).\r\n2. **Log Analytics workspace** — the same workspace selected in the *Machines Log Analytics Workspace* parameter above.\r\n3. **Permissions**: `Monitoring Contributor` (or `Contributor`) on the resource group that will host the DCR, plus rights to create Data Collection Rule Associations on each Arc machine.\r\n4. **Region match**: the DCR must be created in the same Azure region as the Log Analytics workspace.\r\n\r\n---"
                  },
                  "name": "dcr-setup-prereqs"
                },
                {
                  "type": 1,
                  "content": {
                    "json": "### 🎯 Required Performance Counters\r\n\r\n| Chart | Required counter(s) |\r\n|-------|---------------------|\r\n| CPU Usage — Top 5 Clusters | `\\Processor(_Total)\\% Processor Time` |\r\n| Memory Usage — Top 5 Clusters | `\\Memory\\Committed Bytes`, `\\Memory\\Available Bytes` |\r\n| Storage % Used — Top 5 Clusters | `\\LogicalDisk(*)\\% Free Space`, `\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\% Used Space`, `\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\% Free Space` |\r\n| Storage Latency — Top 5 Clusters | `\\LogicalDisk(*)\\Avg. Disk sec/Read`, `\\LogicalDisk(*)\\Avg. Disk sec/Write`, `\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\Avg. Disk sec/Read`, `\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\Avg. Disk sec/Write` |\r\n| Storage IOPS — Top 5 Clusters | `\\LogicalDisk(*)\\Disk Transfers/sec`, `\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\Disk Transfers/sec` |\r\n| Network Throughput — Top 5 Clusters | `\\Network Interface(*)\\Bytes Total/sec` |\r\n\r\nAll counters are sampled every **60 seconds** and flow into the `Perf` table via the `Microsoft-Perf` stream. `Heartbeat` is supplied automatically by AMA and does not need to be configured.\r\n\r\n---"
                  },
                  "name": "dcr-setup-required-counters"
                },
                {
                  "type": 1,
                  "content": {
                    "json": "### 🪵 Required Windows Event Log (Storage Forecast tiles only)\r\n\r\nThe **Storage capacity / volume-size forecast** charts on the *Multi-Node* and *Single-Node* sub-tabs read **per-volume size and used-space figures** that exist **only** in **Event ID 3002** of the `Microsoft-Windows-SDDC-Management/Operational` event log. Those values are **not** in the `Perf` table, so they require a `windowsEventLogs` data source.\r\n\r\n> **⚠️ Not collected by default.** The Azure Local **AMA DCR** that ships out-of-the-box (`AzureStackHCI-AzureLocal-Default-DCR`) declares only `performanceCounters` — it does **not** include `windowsEventLogs`. Storage capacity forecasts will be empty until you add this event log to a DCR associated with each Azure Local node.\r\n\r\n**Add via Portal — Custom log query:**\r\n1. Open your DCR → **Data sources → Windows Event Logs → Add data source** (or edit the existing one).\r\n2. Select **Custom** and paste the XPath query: `Microsoft-Windows-SDDC-Management/Operational!*[System[(EventID=3002)]]`\r\n3. Save. Event records flow into the `Event` table (`EventLog == \"Microsoft-Windows-SDDC-Management/Operational\"`, `EventID == 3002`).\r\n\r\nThe ARM template below already includes this `windowsEventLogs` block.\r\n\r\nLatest update notes: SDDC dependency has been **removed** from all CPU, Memory, Storage Latency / IOPS, and Network Throughput tiles in v1.0.1 — those now use only `Heartbeat` + `Perf` counters and the ARG-derived `ClusterNodeMap`. SDDC remains required only for the **Storage volume-size forecasts**.\r\n\r\n---",
                    "style": "info"
                  },
                  "name": "dcr-setup-required-eventlogs"
                },
                {
                  "type": 1,
                  "content": {
                    "json": "### ✅ Recommended — Add Counters via the Portal (Custom counter specifier)\r\n\r\nThe Azure Portal's DCR editor offers a fixed dropdown of performance objects: `Processor`, `Processor Information`, `LogicalDisk`, `Memory`, `Network Interface`, `Process`, `System`. It **does not list** `Cluster CSV File System` or `Cluster Shared Volume` — the counters that report real latency, IOPS and capacity data for Storage Spaces Direct (S2D) CSV volumes. Without them, the **Storage %, Storage Latency and Storage IOPS** charts only reflect the OS / boot disk.\r\n\r\nHowever, the portal **does** let you add any counter by path via the **Custom counter specifier** input. This is the **easiest and safest** method because it **adds to** an existing DCR instead of replacing it — no risk of losing previously configured counters.\r\n\r\n**Steps:**\r\n1. Open **Azure Monitor → Data Collection Rules** (or the [DCR blade](https://portal.azure.com/#view/Microsoft_Azure_Monitoring/DataCollectionRulesBlade)) and select the DCR already associated with your Azure Local nodes — or create a new Windows DCR and associate it with your Arc machines.\r\n2. Under **Data sources → Performance Counters**, click **Add data source** (or edit the existing Performance Counters data source).\r\n3. Set **Performance counter selection mode** to **Custom**.\r\n4. In the **Custom counter specifier** box, enter one counter path per entry (click **Add** between each). Paste the counter paths from the table above, for example:\r\n   - `\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\% Used Space`\r\n   - `\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\% Free Space`\r\n   - `\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\Avg. Disk sec/Read`\r\n   - `\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\Avg. Disk sec/Write`\r\n   - `\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\Disk Transfers/sec`\r\n5. Leave **Sample rate** at **60** seconds and save.\r\n\r\nData typically begins flowing within a few minutes. Repeat for any other counters from the required list that aren't already collected.\r\n\r\nPrefer source-controlled, repeatable deployments? Toggle **🛠️ Show Alternative ARM / CLI Deployment** below to reveal an ARM template plus matching `az` commands.\r\n\r\n---"
                  },
                  "name": "dcr-setup-portal-method"
                },
                {
                  "type": 9,
                  "content": {
                    "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                    "parameters": [
                      {
                        "id": "dcr-arm-alt-toggle",
                        "version": "KqlParameterItem/1.0",
                        "name": "ShowDCRArmAlt",
                        "label": "🛠️ Show Alternative ARM / CLI Deployment",
                        "type": 10,
                        "isRequired": true,
                        "typeSettings": {
                          "additionalResourceOptions": [],
                          "showDefault": false
                        },
                        "jsonData": "[{\"value\": \"yes\", \"label\": \"Yes - Show ARM / CLI Alternative\"}, {\"value\": \"no\", \"label\": \"No - Hide ARM / CLI Alternative\"}]",
                        "value": "no"
                      }
                    ],
                    "style": "pills",
                    "queryType": 0,
                    "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces"
                  },
                  "name": "dcr-arm-alt-toggle-param"
                },
                {
                  "type": 12,
                  "content": {
                    "version": "NotebookGroup/1.0",
                    "groupType": "editable",
                    "items": [
                      {
                        "type": 1,
                        "content": {
                          "json": "### 🛠️ Alternative — ARM / CLI Deployment\r\n\r\nUse the ARM template below if you prefer source-controlled, repeatable deployments or want to stand up a dedicated DCR for these counters.\r\n\r\n> **IMPORTANT:** ARM deployments are **declarative and replace the entire `properties` block** of a Data Collection Rule. Redeploying this template against the name of an **existing** DCR will overwrite its `performanceCounters`, `streams`, `destinations` and `dataFlows` — any counters you previously added (e.g. `Process`, custom application counters) will be removed.\r\n>\r\n> **Safe options:**\r\n> 1. **Recommended — deploy as a new DCR** with a unique `dcrName` (e.g. `dcr-azurelocal-capacity-perf`) and associate it **alongside** your existing DCRs. A single Arc-enabled machine can have multiple DCR associations; counter collection is the union of all associated DCRs.\r\n> 2. **Merging into an existing DCR** — first export the current definition (`az monitor data-collection rule show -n <name> -g <rg> -o json > existing-dcr.json`), merge the counter specifiers from the template below into its `properties.dataSources.performanceCounters` array, then redeploy.\r\n>\r\n> Always review the counter list against what you already collect before deploying.\r\n\r\n---",
                          "style": "warning"
                        },
                        "name": "dcr-setup-alt-banner"
                      },
                      {
                        "type": 1,
                        "content": {
                          "json": "### 📄 Sample ARM Template\r\n\r\nSave the template below as `dcr-azurelocal-capacity.json` and deploy it to the resource group that will host the DCR. Fill in your Log Analytics workspace resource ID when prompted (or via a parameters file).\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\n  \"$schema\": \"https://schema.management.azure.com/schemas/2019-04-01/deploymentTemplate.json#\",\n  \"contentVersion\": \"1.0.0.0\",\n  \"parameters\": {\n    \"dcrName\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"defaultValue\": \"dcr-azurelocal-capacity-perf\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"description\": \"Name of the Data Collection Rule.\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"location\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"defaultValue\": \"[resourceGroup().location]\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"description\": \"Region for the DCR. Must match the Log Analytics workspace region.\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"workspaceResourceId\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"metadata\": {\n        \"description\": \"Resource ID of the Log Analytics workspace used by the LENS workbook.\"\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"resources\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"Microsoft.Insights/dataCollectionRules\",\n      \"apiVersion\": \"2022-06-01\",\n      \"name\": \"[parameters('dcrName')]\",\n      \"location\": \"[parameters('location')]\",\n      \"kind\": \"Windows\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"dataSources\": {\n          \"performanceCounters\": [\n            {\n              \"name\": \"azureLocalCapacityCounters\",\n              \"streams\": [\n                \"Microsoft-Perf\"\n              ],\n              \"samplingFrequencyInSeconds\": 60,\n              \"counterSpecifiers\": [\n                \"\\\\Processor(_Total)\\\\% Processor Time\",\n                \"\\\\Memory\\\\Committed Bytes\",\n                \"\\\\Memory\\\\Available Bytes\",\n                \"\\\\LogicalDisk(*)\\\\% Free Space\",\n                \"\\\\LogicalDisk(*)\\\\Avg. Disk sec/Read\",\n                \"\\\\LogicalDisk(*)\\\\Avg. Disk sec/Write\",\n                \"\\\\LogicalDisk(*)\\\\Disk Transfers/sec\",\n                \"\\\\Network Interface(*)\\\\Bytes Total/sec\",\n                \"\\\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\\\% Used Space\",\n                \"\\\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\\\% Free Space\",\n                \"\\\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\\\Avg. Disk sec/Read\",\n                \"\\\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\\\Avg. Disk sec/Write\",\n                \"\\\\Cluster CSV File System(*)\\\\Disk Transfers/sec\"\n              ]\n            }\n          ],\n          \"windowsEventLogs\": [\n            {\n              \"name\": \"azureLocalSddcEvents\",\n              \"streams\": [\n                \"Microsoft-Event\"\n              ],\n              \"xPathQueries\": [\n                \"Microsoft-Windows-SDDC-Management/Operational!*[System[(EventID=3002)]]\"\n              ]\n            }\n          ]\n        },\n        \"destinations\": {\n          \"logAnalytics\": [\n            {\n              \"name\": \"laDestination\",\n              \"workspaceResourceId\": \"[parameters('workspaceResourceId')]\"\n            }\n          ]\n        },\n        \"dataFlows\": [\n          {\n            \"streams\": [\n              \"Microsoft-Perf\"\n            ],\n            \"destinations\": [\n              \"laDestination\"\n            ]\n          },\n          {\n            \"streams\": [\n              \"Microsoft-Event\"\n            ],\n            \"destinations\": [\n              \"laDestination\"\n            ]\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"outputs\": {\n    \"dcrResourceId\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"value\": \"[resourceId('Microsoft.Insights/dataCollectionRules', parameters('dcrName'))]\"\n    }\n  }\n}\r\n```"
                        },
                        "name": "dcr-setup-arm-template"
                      },
                      {
                        "type": 1,
                        "content": {
                          "json": "### 🚀 Deployment Steps\r\n\r\n**1. Deploy the DCR** (replace `<rg>`, `<subId>`, `<la-rg>`, `<la-workspace>`):\r\n\r\n```bash\r\naz deployment group create \\\r\n  --resource-group <rg> \\\r\n  --template-file dcr-azurelocal-capacity.json \\\r\n  --parameters workspaceResourceId=/subscriptions/<subId>/resourceGroups/<la-rg>/providers/Microsoft.OperationalInsights/workspaces/<la-workspace>\r\n```\r\n\r\n**2. Capture the DCR resource ID** from the deployment output (or from the portal).\r\n\r\n**3. Associate the DCR to every Azure Local node** (Arc-enabled machine). Loop over the machines in the cluster's resource group:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nDCR_ID=$(az deployment group show -g <rg> -n dcr-azurelocal-capacity --query properties.outputs.dcrResourceId.value -o tsv)\r\n\r\naz connectedmachine list -g <cluster-rg> --query \"[].id\" -o tsv | while read MACHINE_ID; do\r\n  az monitor data-collection rule association create \\\r\n    --name azlocal-capacity-dcra \\\r\n    --resource \"$MACHINE_ID\" \\\r\n    --rule-id \"$DCR_ID\"\r\ndone\r\n```\r\n\r\nData typically begins flowing within a few minutes. The charts above will then show per-cluster CPU, memory, storage %, latency, IOPS and network throughput — including CSV volumes.\r\n\r\n---"
                        },
                        "name": "dcr-setup-deploy-steps"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "conditionalVisibility": {
                    "parameterName": "ShowDCRArmAlt",
                    "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                    "value": "yes"
                  },
                  "name": "dcr-setup-arm-alt-group"
                },
                {
                  "type": 11,
                  "content": {
                    "version": "LinkItem/1.0",
                    "style": "nav",
                    "links": [
                      {
                        "id": "dcr-ama-perf-docs",
                        "cellValue": "https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/agents/data-collection-performance",
                        "linkTarget": "Url",
                        "linkLabel": "📚 AMA Performance Counters",
                        "style": "link"
                      },
                      {
                        "id": "dcr-arm-reference",
                        "cellValue": "https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/templates/microsoft.insights/datacollectionrules",
                        "linkTarget": "Url",
                        "linkLabel": "📘 DCR ARM Reference",
                        "style": "link"
                      },
                      {
                        "id": "dcr-association-docs",
                        "cellValue": "https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/agents/data-collection-rule-associations",
                        "linkTarget": "Url",
                        "linkLabel": "🔗 DCR Associations",
                        "style": "link"
                      },
                      {
                        "id": "dcr-portal-blade",
                        "cellValue": "https://portal.azure.com/#view/Microsoft_Azure_Monitoring/DataCollectionRulesBlade",
                        "linkTarget": "Url",
                        "linkLabel": "🧭 DCR Portal Blade",
                        "style": "link"
                      },
                      {
                        "id": "csv-perf-counters-docs",
                        "cellValue": "https://learn.microsoft.com/windows-server/failover-clustering/manage-cluster-shared-volumes",
                        "linkTarget": "Url",
